1. Create an EC2 instance/VPS

2. Apache2Installation Command for ubuntu
	sudo apt update
	sudo apt install apache2 -y

3. Start and Enable Apache2
	sudo systemctl start apache2
	sudo systemctl enable apache2

4. verification
	sudo systemctl status apache2
             or
	curl localhost on your  machine
			 or
	type your instance ip in browser and check default HTML page

Note:
	if enable to hit browser then check security config outbound rule for http traffic

5. Restart Aache2
	sudo systemctl estart apache2

6. Change listening port
	sudo nano/etc/apache2/ports.conf and change Listen 80 to the port that you want
	



